cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with resource allocation in wireless networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses the average packet sojourn time as the performance metric, which is a measure of information flow. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses an interactive queueing model to characterize the flow level performance, which is a system-level approach. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions traffic variations in overlapping cells, which could be related to multimedia traffic. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper focuses on optimizing the performance metric of average packet sojourn time, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
